<section xml:id="sec-Linear-inequalities" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Linear Inequalities</title>

  <introduction>

    <p>
      A linear inequality is a statement that compares two linear expressions using symbols such as:
    </p>

    <p>
      Less than <m>\rightarrow</m> (<m>\lt</m>)
    </p>
    
    <p>
      Greater than <m>\rightarrow</m> (<m>\gt</m>)  
    </p>
    <p>
      Less than or equal to <m>\rightarrow</m> (<m>\le</m>)  
    </p>
    <p>
      Greater than or equal to <m>\rightarrow</m> (<m>\ge</m>)
    </p>
    <p>
    These inequalities express a range of possible values rather than just one specific solution.
    </p>
  </introduction>

    <subsection xml:id="subsec-Applying_Linear_Inequality_Symbols_to_inequality_statements">
      <title>Applying Linear Inequality Symbols to Inequality Statements.</title>
      
      <activity>

       <p>
          <term>Work in Groups.</term>
        </p>

        <sidebyside>

          <p>

            <ol>

              <li>
                
